summary: 10/09/1993: Unidentified gunmen wounded a military officer in Cairo who had been prosecuting Islamic militants on terrorism charges. Al-Gamaa al-Islamiyya claimed responsibility for the attack.
target1: Egypt's Chief Military Prosecutor in Cairo
motive: The attack was perpetrated as revenge for the death of a fellow extremist by Torture.
scite1: "Suspected Islamic Militants wound Senior Military Prosecutor,” Agence France Presse, October 9, 1993.
scite2: Khaled Dawoud, “Suspected Extremists Target Military Prosecutor,” The Associated Press, October 9, 1993.
scite3: "Egyptian Military Prosecutor Wounded in Attack,” Xinhua, October 9, 1993.
